{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586188"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:27:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:27:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15072"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15072","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15072"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.82,0.12,0,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7760"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64415"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7760","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7760"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15072"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49847"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18941"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18944"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21223"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64415","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64415"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIncidental findings on CT scans are relatively common, being found in some 20 - 40% of such investigations. Many of these \u0027incidentalomas\u0027 focus on the kidney. When a renal mass is found it is important to determine whether the mass is benign or malignant as this will impact on patient management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a malignant renal tumour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Angiomyolipoma","Clear cell carcinoma","Multiple myeloma","Oncocytoma","Papillary adenoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClear cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common malignant renal tumour, accounting for approximately 75% of renal cell carcinomas. \u003Cstrong\u003EOncocytomas\u003C/strong\u003E are benign epithelial tumours characterised by large cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPapillary adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E are benign tumours defined as being less than 5 mm in size with a papillary or tubular architecture. \u003Cstrong\u003EAngiomyolipomas\u003C/strong\u003E are benign mesenchymal tumours composed of blood vessels, smooth muscle, and mature adipose tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMultiple myeloma\u003C/strong\u003E is a haematological malignancy that primarily affects the bone marrow and is not a primary renal tumour, although it can cause renal complications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Clear cell carcinoma is the most common malignant renal tumour.","Multiple myeloma is a haematological malignancy, not a primary renal tumour."],"references":["Desai A, Faquin WC, Iafrate AJ, Rivera MN, Jaquinet A, Troulis MJ. Clear cell carcinoma: a comprehensive literature review of 254 cases. Int J Oral Maxillofac Surg. 2022 Jun;51(6):705-712. doi: 10.1016/j.ijom.2021.03.018. Epub 2021 Oct 20. PMID: 34686398.","Bahadoram S, Davoodi M, Hassanzadeh S, Bahadoram M, Barahman M, Mafakher L. Renal cell carcinoma: an overview of the epidemiology, diagnosis, and treatment. G Ital Nefrol. 2022 Jun 20;39(3):2022-vol3. PMID: 35819037.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49847"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15072"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49847","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49847"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-23T16:17:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-23T16:18:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7760"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64415"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4933"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urinary","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"dat